ll,{\"className\":\"mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium\",\"children\":\"½ cup\"}],\" \",\"San Marzano tomato sauce\",\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"6\",{\"className\":\"flex items-start gap-3 text-base\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium\",\"children\":\"8 oz\"}],\" \",\"fresh mozzarella\",[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\" — \",\"sliced\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"7\",{\"className\":\"flex items-start gap-3 text-base\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium\",\"children\":\"¼ cup\"}],\" \",\"fresh basil leaves\",\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"8\",{\"className\":\"flex items-start gap-3 text-base\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":[\"\",\" \",\"semolina flour\",[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\" — \",\"for dusting\"]}]]}]]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-2xl font-bold font-serif\",\"children\":\"Instructions\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-serif prose-headings:text-xl prose-headings:mt-8 prose-headings:mb-3 prose-li:marker:text-primary\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-0\",{\"children\":\"This is the pizza that started it all for me. The first time I had a real Margherita in Naples, I understood what all the fuss was about — and I've been chasing that perfect bite ever since.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-0\",{\"children\":\"Tips for Success\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"ul\",\"ul-0\",{\"children\":[\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Use a pizza stone or steel\"}],\" if you have one. Preheat it in the oven for at least 30 minutes at the highest temperature your oven can go.\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-1\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Don't overload the toppings.\"}],\" A true Margherita is about balance — a little sauce, a little cheese, a few basil leaves.\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-2\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Wet mozzarella is the enemy.\"}],\" Pat your fresh mozzarella dry with paper towels before slicing, or you'll end up with a soggy crust.\"]}],\"\\n\"]}],\"\\n\",\"$L25\",\"\\n\",\"$L26\",\"\\n\",\"$L27\"]}]]}]]}],\"$L28\"]}]\n29:T790,\nThis is the pizza that started it all for me. The first time I had a real Margherita in Naples, I understood what all the fuss was about — and I've been chasing that perfect bite ever since.\n\n## Tips for Success\n\n- **Use a pizza stone or steel** if you have one. Preheat it in the oven for at least 30 minutes at the highest temperature your oven can go.\n- **Don't overload the toppings.** A true Margherita is about balance — a little sauce, a little cheese, a few basil leaves.\n- **Wet mozzarella is the enemy.** Pat your fresh mozzarella dry with paper towels before slicing, or you'll end up with a soggy crust.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Activate the yeast.** In a small bowl, combine warm water (110°F / 43°C) and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until foamy.\n\n2. **Make the dough.** In a large bowl, combine flour and salt. Add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Mix until a shaggy dough forms.\n\n3. **Knead.** Turn dough onto a floured surface and knead for 8-10 minutes until smooth and elastic. The dough should spring back when poked.\n\n4. **First rise.** Place dough in an oiled bowl, cover with plastic wrap, and let rise in a warm spot for 1-2 hours until doubled in size.\n\n5. **Shape.** Divide dough into 4 equal balls. On a semolina-dusted surface, stretch each ball into a 10-inch round. Use your hands — don't use a rolling pin, which deflates the bubbles.\n\n6. **Preheat.** Place a pizza stone or inverted baking sheet in the oven and preheat to 500°F (260°C) or the highest setting for at least 30 minutes.\n\n7. **Assemble.** Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce on each dough round. Tear mozzarella pieces and distribute evenly.\n\n8. **Bake.** Slide pizzas onto the hot stone (one at a time) and bake for 8-12 minutes until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbling.\n\n9. **Finish.** Remove from oven, top with fresh basil leaves, drizzle with a little olive oil, and serve immediately.\n\nEnjoy your taste of Naples!\n22:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"print-recipe-card print-only hidden print:block\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center mb-6\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-bold font-serif\",\"children\":\"Appropriated Kitchen\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm italic text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Your Food, My Way\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-3xl font-bold font-serif\",\"children\":\"Classic Margherita Pizza\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm mt-1\",\"children\":[\"Prep: \",\"20 min\",\" | Cook: \",\"12 min\",\" | Total: \",\"32 min\",\" | Serves: \",4]}],[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-2\",\"children\":\"Ingredients\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"2 ¼ tsp\"}],\" \",\"active dry yeast\",\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"1\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"1 cup\"}],\" \",\"warm water\",\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"l